==English==

===Etymology===
From [[Gaelic]] '''Rí''' (meaning [[King]]) and '''Án''' (a suffix meaning [[little]]), thus the name means, Little King.

===Proper noun===
'''Ryan'''
# A male [[given name]]; according to the [[United States]] 1990 [[census]] [http://www.census.gov/genealogy/names/dist.male.first], ''Ryan'' was the 49th most popular male given name

====Translations====
*Japanese: ライアン (Hepburn transliteration system: raian)(IPA: ɽaian)
*Korean: 라이언 (official South Korean transliteration system: ra-i-eon)(IPA: laiʌn)
*Thai: ไรอัน
*Chinese: 小王 (literally, little king)
*Cyrillic: Раен

